## Troubleshooting

**The game crashes on launch.**

Try the following steps in order:

1. Force-close the app and reopen it.
2. Restart your device.
3. Ensure your device is running iOS 16.0 or later.
4. Check for app updates in the App Store.
5. If the issue persists, delete and reinstall the app. Your Game Center progress and any purchases will be preserved.

**The game runs slowly or drops frames.**

Close other apps running in the background to free up memory. Space Station: Defender is optimized for most devices, but older hardware may experience occasional slowdowns during large wave encounters with many enemies and turrets active simultaneously.

**My progress was lost.**

Game progress is saved locally on your device. If you deleted and reinstalled the app, local save data may have been lost. Game Center achievements and leaderboard scores are stored in the cloud and will sync back automatically. In-app purchases can be restored via the "Restore Purchases" button in the store.

**Audio isn't working.**

Check that your device is not in Silent mode (the physical switch on the side of your device). Also verify that the in-game audio settings have music and sound effects enabled.

